title: Learn CPR
primaryText: You should first call your local emergency number
secondaryText: if you see a teen or adult suddenly collapse and is not responsive and not breathing normally.
tertiaryText: Push hard and fast in the center of the chest at the rate of 100 to 120 beats per minute, such as the beat of the classic disco song Stayin Alive...
speakTextOne: According to the American Heart Association, you should first call your local emergency number if you see a teen or adult suddenly collapse and is not responsive and not breathing normally. Then, push hard and fast in the center of the chest at the rate of 100 to 120 beats per minute, such as the beat of the classic disco song Stayin Alive... Here is how fast you should push on the chest.
